Program: The History Hour
Title: When Belgium Banned Coca Cola
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqm5
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 21 Oct 2018
A strange illness strikes Belgian teenagers, Brazil's forgotten Amazon war, diverting Mount Etna's lava, arguments over aid and trade in the UK, and the 1973 oil crisis. (Photo: A poster saying 'out of order' is stuck on a Coca Cola vending machine in Mouscron, Belgium in 1999. Credit: Philippe Huguen/AFP/Getty Images). Show less